We will keep this information for as long as necessary. After we have responded to you, feedback will be anonymised and we will use it to help improve our services.
Details about how we use your personal information for direct marketing is set out below.
Who we share your personal information with
We routinely share your name, email address, billing/delivery address and account activity with trusted third party services. This data sharing enables us to provide customer support, process payments, supply goods and services to you, and improve the services and products we offer to you. Some of those third party recipients may be based outside the European Economic Area or process your personal information outside of the European Economic Area. We will share personal information with law enforcement or other authorities if required by applicable law.
Our Service providers
. These are external companies that We use to help Us run our business (e.g. order fulfilment, payment processing, fraud detection and identity verification, website operation, market research companies, support services, promotions, website development, data analysis, CRC, etc.). Service providers, and their selected staff, are only allowed to access and use your Personal Data on Our behalf for the specific tasks that they have been requested to carry out, based on our instructions, and are required to keep your Personal Data confidential and secure. Where required by applicable law, you can obtain a full list of the providers processing your Personal Data.
Marketing partners.
We may pseudonymise your data through a technique called "hashing". We may use pseudonymised data with our partners (such as Facebook), this allows us to measure the effectiveness of our advertising, improve our marketing practices, and helps us deliver more relevant advertising to you and people like you (including on social media). This also ensures that as an existing customer you are not included in marketing campaigns designed to attract new customers.
International transfers of your information
EU data protection rules apply to the European Economic Area (EEA), which includes all EU countries and non-EU countries Iceland, Liechtenstein and Norway.
We will not transfer your personal data outside of the EEA and will not transfer your personal data to any organisation that would process your personal data outside the EEA unless there has been an adequacy decision made by European Commission that there is an adequate level of protection for personal data transferred in the relevant country or there is a suitable safeguard in place, such as standard contractual clauses or the
EU-US Privacy Shield
framework.
If you would like to obtain a copy of the safeguards we have in place for the transfer of personal information outside of the EEA please contact
hello@simplycook.com
5. Cookies
A cookie is a small text file which is placed onto your device (e.g. computer, smartphone, tablet) when you use our website. We use cookies to help us recognise you and your device and record information about your preferences or past actions.
For further information on our use of cookies, please see our
Cookie Policy
.
For general information on cookies, please visit
www.allaboutcookies.org
.
6. Marketing
We would like to send you information about products, services, competitions, and special offers which may be of interest to you. Where we have your consent or it is in our legitimate interests to do so, we may do this by post, email, telephone, text message (SMS), or automated call.
If you have previously agreed to being contacted in this way, you can unsubscribe at any time by:
- contacting us at
hello@simplycook.com
- using the 'unsubscribe' link in emails or 'STOP' number in texts
It may take up to 5 working days for this to be completed.
For more information on your rights in relation to marketing, please see the
Your Rights
page.
7. Your rights
Under the GDPR you have a number of important rights free of charge. Please see the
Your Rights
page for details of these rights and information on how to exercise them.
8. Keeping your personal information secure
We have appropriate security measures in place to prevent personal information from being accidentally lost, used, or accessed in an unauthorised way. We limit access to your personal information to those who have a genuine business need to know it. Those processing your information will do so only in an authorised manner and are subject to a duty of confidentiality.
We also have procedures in place to deal with any suspected data security breach. We will notify you and any applicable regulator of a suspected data security breach where we are legally required to do so.
9. How to complain
We hope that we can resolve any query or concern you raise about our use of your information.
The General Data Protection Regulation also gives you right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority, in particular in the European Union (or European Economic Area) state where you work, normally live or where any alleged infringement of data protection laws occurred. The supervisory authority in the UK is the Information Commissioner who may be contacted at
ico.org.uk
or telephone:
0303 123 1113
.
10. Changes to this privacy policy
This privacy policy was published on 23rd May 2018 and last updated on 15th November 2023.
We may change this privacy policy from time to time, when this is a significant change affecting you we will inform you via email to your registered address.
11. How to contact us
If you have any questions about this privacy notice or the information we hold about you, please send an email to
hello@simplycook.com
or write to SimplyCook, Unit D, Discovery House, Juniper Drive, London, SW18 1UY.
